author: @idonotknowwhyyoutubeletsyo5893
comment:
edit after watching another teardown: There are two 2x50W amplifiers, none of them run at full power. They can only reach 50W  after they reach 10%THD.
This video revealed exactly what I was expecting. The electronics(cables and amplifier components) inside are made to handle 70W at best. Seems like 2x5W tweeters, 2x10W mid-range drivers and a 30-50W subwoofer driver.
As a studied Electrotechnic/mechanic, I can't imagine the subwoofer being rated over 40W with the shallow magnet and tiny surround. Not enough excursion to reach that even if it was given the power from somewhere.

comment:
MaxSound traditional is not about MaxSound effect. This new Xsound Plus 2 sounds very V shaped not neutral. Which makes the sound muddy. Which Alan Ross mentioned in his detailed youtube video for this product. Tribit listened to the complained and launched a new preset called "MaxSound Traditional" for people who prefer the older mode's MaxSound Plus neutral sounding for crystal clear sound. 

Alan Ross recommends playing this in MaxSound Traditional mode for best natural sounding experience. For bass, Xbass will do.

author: @suryavishwanath8564
comment: i have both..and listened to both carefully...here is my review on this.xsound plus 2 sounds very clear (voices sounds soo clear) and bass is tight and punchy..but stormbox 2 sounds louder with thumpy warm bass..like vibrating in the air bass..punchy bass is like sharp bass but less vibrating in the air..but stormbox bass is more bassier..but xsound 2 plus osund more crystal clear and bass is firing in front of you, so you can listen to bass frequncies which storm box 2 might not produce..this you will find in some songs where different freq are bass are used...so my verdict, both are different speakers for differnet usage...stormbox 2 is for outdoor purposes and 360 degree sound expereince..the sounds is louder and richer and you can here the same quality of sound in any direction you stand....but its not the case with xsound plus 2...thsi will only sound clear and awesome if its facing you..if you go in other direction you wont will loose sound , so its better used indoors that too, when you are facing it only..like in a desk or under computer..it will sound very detailed and with good bass......so based on whether u will be using indoor or outdoors, you can buy anyone..both sounds fantastic, but storm box 2 will sound a bit louder due to big drivers and extra wattage and you will feel the difference for sure..like 10% - 15% it will sound louder than xsound go 2..i have given you a better perspective, so you better buy ...now sale is going on...

author: @priyadarshanmusicproductio4253
comment:
That kind of speakers are not Low-Mid (Frequency) speakers. These are Full Range woofer Speaker..
Low Mid Speaker meh sirf low frequency (bass) & mid frequency ka awaz hi nikalta hai, high frequency (treble) nahi niklega... Alag se Tweeter (Hf) driver speaker lagana parta hai.
Lekin full range speaker meh equal sabh frequency ka awaz nikal dega.

author: @narendrairengbam112
comment:
The xsound plus 2 has more low end deep bass. The lower frequency range starting from 50hz compared to 70hz of stormbox 2 is obvious. Xsound plus 2 for deep boomy bass lovers and strombox for brighter sound with more loud and clear mids. 

Loudness wise, the difference is negligible, also one is 360 and the other is one directional, so 4 watt difference isnt a big deal. 

I have the xiaomi outdoor 30 w and it is more comparable to the xsound plus 2, rather then the stormbox. Because the stormbox cant keep up with the deep bass the xiaomi has, the xsound plus does it better.

author: @narendrairengbam112
comment:
Please compare this with portronics Sound Drum P. 
The only speaker in 15 to 30 watt range that I want every other speaker to compare in terms of loudness and bass is the one and only portronics sound drum P. That's still the king of 20watt speakers to me. There's hardly any speaker at that price point and wattage that can beat this speaker in terms of loudness, clarity and bass. That speaker is just amazing and unbelievable for just 2000 rupees from portronics. Only minor drawback is the battery life, it last for about 3 hours only at loud volume. If it could last for atleast 4 to 5 hours at 80 to 100 volume, then there's no point buying other speakers. Portronics Sound Drum P is the unbeatable king.

It could be the speaker that is unable to function properly with Apple devices especially Mac to compensate the delay

author: @narendrairengbam112
comment:
Nope, it cannot kill the jbl flip 6. May be for the price it is good value, better than the flip, also with the battery life. But sound wise, it is a tad bit inferior to jbl flip. First of all flip 6 is louder and has more deeper bass that's also punchy with sharper vocals and brighter audio. This one has very good mids and crisp sound but bass isn't the best and loudness is a bit lower even with the 34 wattage, that's the nature of tribit. Little less loud for the wattage. 

Yeah 360 sound and battery wise, it is better. Not the sound though.
